name: KS Sec. of State
tweet: Poll worker recruitment is consistently mentioned as a priority for our local election officials. Volunteers and temporary election workers play an essential role in administering elections and ensuring Election Day runs smoothly. Apply online:  https://t.co/geoVtxrYtU #ksleg

name: KS Sec. of State
tweet: Did You Know: The Kansas Secretary of State routinely updates and publishes election standards. Election standards are a guide for local election officers on how to administer elections in their county, and can be viewed on our website.  https://t.co/ObIvI6jZiq #ksleg

name: KS Sec. of State
tweet: #FactFriday All voters reserve the right to a secret ballot. Election workers are responsible for protecting a voter's choice from being viewable or knowable by others - including the election worker. Therefore, once a ballot has been cast, it cannot be traced to the voter #ksleg

name: KS Sec. of State
tweet: One of the best ways to keep your business in good standing is to file your annual report prior to the deadline – April 15. Documents may be filed on our website:  https://t.co/h037erzp5U  For assistance, please contact our Business Services Division at sos@ks.gov or 785.296.4564.

name: KS Sec. of State
tweet: Did You Know: State law requires voters to show valid ID when casting a ballot in person. Additionally, signature verification is required when submitting an advance by mail ballot application and on the completed ballot. #ksleg  https://t.co/YQLNxR89cr

name: KS Sec. of State
